-- Investors With 39.3% of Greek Debt Will Join Swap, IIF Says
-- B y   M a r i a   P e t r a k i s
-- 2012-03-07T12:36:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-07/investors-holding-39-3-of-greek-debt-will-participate-in-swap-iif-says.html
Thirty investors in Greek securities
have agreed to participate in a Greek debt swap, according to an
e-mailed statement from the  Institute of International Finance .  The thirty members of the private creditor-investor
committee for  Greece  who plan to participate in the swap hold an
aggregate 81 billion euros of Greek debt, or 39.3 percent of the
Greek debt eligible for the swap, according to the email today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maria Petrakis at 
 mpetrakis@bloomberg.net  